Description: Fragment of foot and lower body of Fikellura style painted pottery neck-amphora; Belly, volutes, crescents, tongues.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Findspot 52 W (west?), south-eastern quarter of the Saite enclosure (so-called "Camp"), area of ironsmith's workshops.
Curator's comments: Findspot determined by '52 W’ scratched on the base of object. Attributed to the Volute Zone Group.
